library(ggridges)
library(leaflet)
library(p8105.datasets)

data(nyc_airbnb)

nyc_airbnb = 
  nyc_airbnb |>
  rename(borough = neighbourhood_group) |>
  mutate(stars = review_scores_location / 2)

Brainstorm questions

  • Where are AirBNBs expensive?
    • Borough? Neighborhood?
    • Do other factors (room type) affect price? What about rating
  • How long are AirBNBs active?
    • Are AirBNBs illegal and do they get shut down?
  • Which units have the most availbability?
  • How is review score impacted by location?
  • How many apts are run by one host?

Do some EDA

  count(borough)

nyc_airbnb |>
  group_by(borough, room_type) |>
  summarize(mean_price = mean(price)) |>
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = room_type,
    values_from = mean_price
  )

## `.groups` argument.

nyc_airbnb |>
  ggplot(aes(x = price)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_grid(borough ~ room_type)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

nyc_airbnb |>
  filter(price > 1000, room_type == "Entire home/apt") |>
  ggplot(aes(x = price)) +
  geom_histogram() +
  facet_grid(. ~ borough)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

nyc_airbnb |>
  filter(
    price < 1000,
    room_type == "Entire home/apt",
    borough == "Manhattan") |>
  group_by(neighbourhood) |>
  summarize(
    n_opt = n(),
    mean_price = mean(price)
  ) |>
  arrange(desc(mean_price))

nyc_airbnb |>
  filter(
    price < 1000,
    room_type == "Entire home/apt",
    borough == "Manhattan") |>
  mutate(neighbourhood = fct_reorder(neighbourhood, price)) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = neighbourhood, y = price)) +
  geom_density_ridges()

Try something else

nyc_airbnb |>
  filter(
    price < 1000,
    room_type == "Entire home/apt",
    borough == "Manhattan") |>
  sample_n(500) |>
  leaflet() |>
  addTiles() |>
  addMarkers(~lat, ~long)
nyc_airbnb |>
  filter(
    price < 1000,
    room_type == "Entire home/apt",
    borough == "Manhattan") |>
  sample_n(500) |>
  leaflet() |>
  addProviderTiles(providers$CartoDB.Positron) |>
  addCircleMarkers(~lat, ~long, radius = .5)
